WEBVTT

00:01.334 --> 00:03.402
<i>[ Dennis ]</i>
<i>Oh, wow, dude.</i>
<i>This thing is disgusting.</i>

00:03.404 --> 00:06.405
<i>[ Mac ] There's so</i>
<i>much rust, maybe we should</i>
<i>wipe it with a wet rag.</i>

00:06.407 --> 00:08.107
<i>I'm not gonna do that!</i>
<i>Why not?</i>

00:08.109 --> 00:10.743
Because it's a goddamn
circuit breaker, Mac.
We'll get electrocuted.

00:10.745 --> 00:12.578
No, I'm just gonna use
this screwdriver, all right?

00:12.580 --> 00:14.246
It's got a rubber handle.
That'll keep me grounded.

00:14.248 --> 00:16.515
No, I'm pretty sure you
have to be standing
on rubber.

00:16.517 --> 00:19.718
Well, the bottoms of
my shoes are rubber.
Oh, no! You know what it is?

00:19.720 --> 00:21.520
You can't be standing
on the ground at all.

00:21.522 --> 00:23.722
Maybe you should jump up
into midair and do it.
Hmm?

00:23.724 --> 00:26.759
Yeah, if you jump into
the air and grab a live wire,

00:26.761 --> 00:28.227
you... won't
get electrocuted.

00:28.229 --> 00:31.597
But then if you land on
the ground and you're
still holding that wire,

00:31.599 --> 00:32.798
you'll be blown
to bits.

00:32.800 --> 00:34.199
I saw it in
<i>Tango and Cash.</i>

00:34.201 --> 00:36.602
So I'm supposed to risk
my life based on something...

00:36.604 --> 00:37.636
that you saw in the movie
<i>Tango and Cash?</i>

00:37.638 --> 00:41.507
Kurt Russell-- I think--
All right, I'm gonna jam
this thing with a screwdriver.

00:41.509 --> 00:41.907
All right?

00:41.909 --> 00:43.709
The rubber handle
will ground me.
And I'll be safe.

00:43.711 --> 00:44.743
All right.
All right.

00:44.745 --> 00:45.477
Give it a shot.
Okay.

00:45.479 --> 00:47.546
It's all set
to scrape--
Oh, my God!

00:47.548 --> 00:48.180
Holy shit!

00:48.182 --> 00:50.149
[ Frank ]
Whoa, whoa, whoa! Wh-What
the hell are you doing?

00:50.151 --> 00:52.151
It exploded.
You're making it worse!

00:52.153 --> 00:54.153
Bro, you gotta pay somebody
to fix this, man.

00:54.155 --> 00:55.654
No! I'm tired of
spending my money...

00:55.656 --> 00:57.756
every time something goes
wrong in this place.

00:57.758 --> 00:59.358
Well, we can't fix it, Frank!
It's too dangerous!

00:59.360 --> 01:01.593
- It scared the shit
out of me, man.
- Well, get Charlie to do it.

01:01.595 --> 01:04.763
He won't go near the thing.
He's already been electrocuted,
like, 500 times.

01:04.765 --> 01:06.331
Yeah, man.
I think he's starting to
catch on to that.

01:06.333 --> 01:10.569
Dennis, get me a harness
'cause I'll have to be
swinging in the air to do this.

01:10.571 --> 01:11.837
Are you kidding me?
I told you.

01:11.839 --> 01:12.771
Bro, did you
get the flashlights?

01:12.773 --> 01:15.874
<i>Forget about the flashlights!</i>
<i>Check these bad boys out!</i>

01:15.876 --> 01:17.142
They fell off
the back of a truck.
Huh?

01:17.144 --> 01:19.545
Nice grab.
All right, but what
about the flashlights?

01:19.547 --> 01:21.280
Uh, I'm sorry, someone
wasn't paying attention, right?

01:21.282 --> 01:23.782
Free speakers, dude!
Free speakers for the bar!
Free speakers!

01:23.784 --> 01:25.384
Mac, let's plug
these bad boys in.

01:25.386 --> 01:26.685
Yeah!
We don't have any electricity!

01:26.687 --> 01:28.887
That's why we needed
the flashlight.
Careful!

01:28.889 --> 01:30.789
I'm sorry.
I didn't--

01:30.791 --> 01:33.792
- Holy shit.
- [ Dee ]
What is that?

01:34.727 --> 01:36.295
Oh, my God.
Whoa.

01:36.297 --> 01:37.229
That's a...
big bag of drugs.

01:37.231 --> 01:40.199
This is not good, dude.
Somebody's gonna be looking
for those drugs.

01:40.201 --> 01:42.468
Relax, dude.
They're gonna be shit
out of luck 'cause no one--

01:42.470 --> 01:44.603
No one saw us take
the speakers.
Did they?

01:44.605 --> 01:46.605
See us take--
[ Scoffs ]
No.

01:46.607 --> 01:49.241
There you have it.
Look, let's not worry or panic.

01:49.243 --> 01:51.610
This is--
[ Swallows ]
This is a lot of drugs.

01:51.612 --> 01:55.347
But, like, what's the worst
that could happen?
[ Chuckles ]

01:55.349 --> 01:59.551
♪ ♪

02:29.549 --> 02:31.416
Gotta get rid of it.
Yeah.
Drugs are bad news.

02:31.418 --> 02:33.552
Let's get rid of it.
Throw it in the garbage.

02:33.554 --> 02:35.587
Ooh, you can't do that
'cause a kid could find it.
Right.

02:35.589 --> 02:38.457
Burn it.
Well, then we're dealing
with a fume situation.

02:38.459 --> 02:40.425
Yeah, you gotta
wear masks and--
Yeah, it's a whole thing and--

02:40.427 --> 02:42.694
- It's a whole production.
It's a big production.
- All right, then bury it!

02:42.696 --> 02:44.696
<i>Oh, well--</i>
No, see, now we're
back to the kids again.

02:44.698 --> 02:47.266
Because kids run with shovels,
playing in dirt.
Absolutely.

02:47.268 --> 02:49.568
And then one of
them's gonna--
Okay, call the police.

02:49.570 --> 02:52.471
What, are we
gonna just solve
society's drug problem?

02:52.473 --> 02:54.273
You know what I mean?
Is that on us?

02:54.275 --> 02:55.407
No!
Is that on us now?

02:55.409 --> 02:56.675
The community is still going
down the toilet.

02:56.677 --> 02:58.443
So I think what you're saying,
Sweet Dee, is that...

02:58.445 --> 03:01.480
we could use the unsolvable
drug problem in our society...
<i>Mm-hmm.</i>

03:01.482 --> 03:04.383
to fix the solvable
light problem in our bar.

03:04.385 --> 03:05.751
Yes.
Absolutely.
I hear you.

03:05.753 --> 03:07.419
We're saying we're gonna
do the drugs,

03:07.421 --> 03:08.987
and then we're gonna try
and fix all the lights.
No.

03:08.989 --> 03:10.589
Charlie didn't
understand that.
That's asinine.

03:10.591 --> 03:11.890
You want to rewind?
Yeah, we're gonna
flip the drugs.

03:11.892 --> 03:15.327
Make a bunch of money, use that
money to fix the electricity.
Mm-hmm.

03:15.329 --> 03:17.696
All right.
Well, both ways work.
I kinda like my way.

03:17.698 --> 03:18.697
Great plan.
Your way's terrible.

03:18.699 --> 03:19.965
I'm in.
Let's sell these drugs.
You're not in.

03:19.967 --> 03:21.733
Whoop.
Thank you.
And you're not gonna sell them.

03:21.735 --> 03:24.303
We'll do it, Charlie.
Because we found the drugs.

03:24.305 --> 03:25.704
And you're bossy.
Very bossy.

03:25.706 --> 03:27.005
- I'm not bossy.
- Scumbags!

03:27.007 --> 03:29.308
Frank, come on, man.
Look, we're trying to
get some money...

03:29.310 --> 03:30.976
to fix the lights
in our bar because
you won't give it to us.

03:30.978 --> 03:36.248
Back in my day,
only the biggest pieces
of shit dealt drugs.

03:36.250 --> 03:37.382
We're not gonna deal drugs.
Yeah, right.

03:37.384 --> 03:39.651
We're gonna flip it.
We'll flip it once.
It's a onetime flip.

03:39.653 --> 03:41.720
Yeah.
We'll go to your-- that
shady guy Bingo that you know.

03:41.722 --> 03:43.922
Oh, Bingo.
We'll say, you know,
"Here's a pile of drugs.

03:43.924 --> 03:45.457
Give us some money."
And then--
Uh-huh.

03:45.459 --> 03:48.493
Oh, no, no, no.
You don't go to Bingo.
Bingo is my contact.

03:48.495 --> 03:50.562
Uh, I'm sorry. I don't
think you can call dibs...

03:50.564 --> 03:52.598
on a shady
people-smuggler.
You can't do that.

03:52.600 --> 03:54.633
Just do not mention my name!

03:54.635 --> 03:57.803
My God.
Relax, dude, no one's
gonna mention your name.

03:57.805 --> 03:59.738
Hey, Bingo.
Frank sent us.

03:59.740 --> 04:03.842
Frank, huh?
I'm gonna skin that son of
a bitch and wear his face.

04:03.844 --> 04:05.677
- Anyway, what's up?
- Well, we're trying--

04:05.679 --> 04:07.746
- Oh, don't look at me.
- Excuse me?

04:07.748 --> 04:08.847
Look up. Up.
<i>Okay.</i>

04:08.849 --> 04:10.482
Is this good?
That's fine.

04:10.484 --> 04:11.883
- Now speak.
- Uh, okay.

04:11.885 --> 04:16.521
Uh, well, listen, Bingo.
We got a bucket of nose clams
fresh from the sea.

04:16.523 --> 04:20.892
Sweet, delicious nose clams
that are looking for a home
if you follow me.

04:20.894 --> 04:22.194
- Nose clams?
- No. I don't follow you.

04:22.196 --> 04:24.863
I don't know what the hell
you're talking about.
<i>I don't follow either.</i>

04:24.865 --> 04:27.666
Yes, you do.
It's not confusing.
Just everybody settle down.

04:27.668 --> 04:32.404
These are the kind of<i> nose clams</i>
that make you want to dance
the night away.

04:32.406 --> 04:33.905
I don't get what the hell
you're talking about.

04:33.907 --> 04:36.108
I don't even know what
you're talking about.
It's so obvious!

04:36.110 --> 04:38.477
You know what?
It's not obvious.
Now you're being too vague.

04:38.479 --> 04:41.013
You're talking about
dancing clams in the--
[ Groaning ]

04:41.015 --> 04:41.880
What's gonna make you dance?

04:41.882 --> 04:45.017
These are the kind of
nose clams that you crush up
into a line of white powder.

04:45.019 --> 04:47.753
And you snort them
up through your nose.
And they make you high.

04:47.755 --> 04:51.490
You use a dollar bill
or a straw to do it.
They come from Colombia.

04:51.492 --> 04:53.792
They're illegal.
And they rhyme with "propane."

04:53.794 --> 04:55.961
Perfect. You found a perfect
medium ground there.

04:55.963 --> 04:57.796
- So you want to
sell me cocaine?
- Yes!

04:57.798 --> 04:58.964
Why didn't you just
come out and say that?

04:58.966 --> 05:00.432
<i>Instead of dancing around it.</i>
That is so tacky.

05:00.434 --> 05:02.901
- We talked about it in the car.
It's a thing you do.
- It's not tacky.

05:02.903 --> 05:06.872
That is the kindergarten
behavior of drug dealing.
Do you want them or not?

05:06.874 --> 05:09.408
- Yeah, of course I do.
- Oh, great.
Well, here you go.

05:09.410 --> 05:12.377
Thank you.
Eyes, boom.
Yeah.

05:15.048 --> 05:17.349
Oh!
[ Laughs ]
Oh!

05:17.351 --> 05:19.918
<i>Youse two.</i>
<i>We need to talk</i>
<i>to youse, huh?</i>

05:19.920 --> 05:22.387
Oh, shit.
Are you guys gangsters?

05:22.389 --> 05:23.388
[ Together ]
Shut up!

05:23.390 --> 05:25.023
Ah, owe me a Coke.
Listen,

05:25.025 --> 05:27.559
rumor has it that somebody
who works at this bar...

05:27.561 --> 05:29.761
found a certain somethin'
that belongs to us.

05:29.763 --> 05:31.029
<i>A certain somethin'</i>
<i>which may</i>

05:31.031 --> 05:33.065
<i>or may not have fallen off</i>
<i>a certain truck, huh?</i>

05:33.067 --> 05:36.601
And the certain somebody
that we know thinks they saw
that certain someone...

05:36.603 --> 05:38.603
pick it up and take it back
to that certain bar,

05:38.605 --> 05:41.973
which may or may not
be the place that we happen
to be or not be...

05:41.975 --> 05:45.711
talkin' to a couple
of certain somebodies
right this very second.

05:45.713 --> 05:48.480
<i>Capisce?</i>
Huh?

05:48.881 --> 05:50.916
Fellas, we're about
six beers' deep.

05:50.918 --> 05:52.150
So I think you're
gonna have to...

05:52.152 --> 05:54.686
be a little bit more clear
'cause I didn't get
that last part.

05:54.688 --> 05:56.955
I m-- I missed out
on the whole thing
to be honest with you.

05:56.957 --> 05:58.957
I was confused by it.
I'm very confused by the--

05:58.959 --> 06:02.160
I was very confused
by the whole thing to be--
if I'm being honest.

06:02.162 --> 06:06.031
Look, why don't you just
return what belongs to us...

06:06.033 --> 06:10.969
or pay us the 25 G's
that it's worth,
and we'll be square.

06:10.971 --> 06:12.904
Youse got
until Friday, huh?

06:12.906 --> 06:14.406
What happens on Friday?

06:14.408 --> 06:16.007
[ Chuckles ]
[ Chuckles ]

06:16.009 --> 06:18.143
Well, Friday is
the day...

06:18.145 --> 06:21.046
that we may
or may not be forced...

06:21.048 --> 06:22.547
to chop your limbs off...

06:22.549 --> 06:28.887
and distribute them evenly
amongst your friends
and your family.

06:28.889 --> 06:31.623
And that's Friday.

06:31.625 --> 06:32.958
Friday.
Okay.

06:32.960 --> 06:36.027
Well, thanks, gentlemen.
That's-- That's very--
a very clear message.

06:36.029 --> 06:38.797
And we will certainly
get on that right away.
Yeah.

06:38.799 --> 06:41.099
Okay, that's
muched appreciated.

06:41.101 --> 06:42.801
Uh, good day to youse.

06:42.803 --> 06:45.137
And good day to youse.
Come on.
Huh?

06:45.139 --> 06:47.739
What's the matter with you?
Chewin' in my ear all the time.

06:47.741 --> 06:49.841
Friday.
Come on, come on, come on.

06:49.843 --> 06:51.843
Holy shit!

06:53.079 --> 06:54.012
<i>[ Charlie Cheers ]</i>

06:54.014 --> 06:58.917
♪ Guess who sold the drugs
And we can fix
the lights now ♪

06:58.919 --> 06:59.985
The lights are fixed.

06:59.987 --> 07:01.887
Yeah, man.
No shit.
How'd you do that?

07:01.889 --> 07:02.788
We got bigger problems
than that, dude.

07:02.790 --> 07:05.724
The drugs that you just sold,
they belong to the mob.

07:05.726 --> 07:06.858
What?
<i>Yeah, they saw you guys.</i>

07:06.860 --> 07:09.194
Yeah, guys,
real-life actual gangsters.
It was pretty cool.

07:09.196 --> 07:10.862
They came to the bar.
They threatened us.
It was not cool!

07:10.864 --> 07:14.900
Look, the point is, we're
gonna give them the money that
you got from Bingo so it's--

07:14.902 --> 07:17.602
Cool, and then maybe we can
keep a little for ourselves too.

07:17.604 --> 07:19.070
Yeah, well,
how much did you get?
Perfect.

07:19.072 --> 07:20.806
Oh, dude--
a one, a two,

07:20.808 --> 07:21.940
a $300!
Hello.

07:21.942 --> 07:24.776
You guys, those drugs
were worth 25 grand!

07:24.778 --> 07:26.678
Oh, shit!
Are you serious?

07:26.680 --> 07:28.113
<i>Yes!</i>
Now, see now?
I told you.

07:28.115 --> 07:29.881
I asked for more money.
What?

07:29.883 --> 07:30.882
Yes, I did.
No, you didn't!

07:30.884 --> 07:33.552
I was using
"Dead Presidents" as a cover.
You didn't get that?

07:33.554 --> 07:37.222
He said to the man
he wanted many, many
thousands of green people...

07:37.224 --> 07:38.890
[ Together ]
from history times.

07:38.892 --> 07:40.225
Oh, my God.
We are so screwed.

07:40.227 --> 07:43.528
How are we gonna get
25 grand by Friday?
I get that.

07:45.898 --> 07:47.999
Don't look at me.
You made this bed.

07:48.001 --> 07:50.669
You're sleeping in it.
This is a life lesson for you.

07:50.671 --> 07:52.838
Frank, this is not the time
to be throwing down
life lessons, all right?

07:52.840 --> 07:55.607
We are going to
get whacked off by
a bunch of scary Italian guys.

07:55.609 --> 07:56.675
Did they say they were
gonna whack us off?

07:56.677 --> 07:58.543
They implied they wanted
to whack us all off!
Okay.

07:58.545 --> 08:01.146
Nobody's gonna get
whacked off today, okay?
Listen.

08:01.148 --> 08:03.882
We're gonna take the money.
We'll go get our drugs
back from Bingo.

08:03.884 --> 08:06.651
We'll give it to the mob.
And we'll pretend none of this
ever happened.

08:06.653 --> 08:08.687
And this time,
I'll do the talking!
Okay.

08:08.689 --> 08:09.621
Just keep my name out of it.

08:09.623 --> 08:12.157
Frank said to tell you
to sell us back our drugs.

08:12.159 --> 08:13.658
Okay.
No problem.

08:13.660 --> 08:14.860
Good.
Good.
Great.

08:14.862 --> 08:16.127
Excellent.
Problem solved.

08:16.129 --> 08:17.662
- $5,000.
- What?

08:17.664 --> 08:20.098
Oh, boy!
Just an hour ago,
you gave us 300 for 'em.

08:20.100 --> 08:22.367
- Yeah, man.
- Yeah, I don't recall that.

08:22.369 --> 08:23.935
<i>[ Charlie ]</i>
<i>Come on!</i>
All right.

08:23.937 --> 08:27.873
- What can we get for 300 then?
- Uh, you want an exotic bird?

08:27.875 --> 08:28.607
[ All Clamoring ]

08:28.609 --> 08:31.276
If you're gonna play this game,
we need to buy something
from you...

08:31.278 --> 08:35.013
that we can sell back to other
people at a higher price.
Yeah.

08:35.015 --> 08:36.815
Okay.
OxyContin.

08:36.817 --> 08:38.683
It's a very popular pill
these days.

08:38.685 --> 08:41.253
And I happen to have
a whole shitload of it.

08:41.255 --> 08:42.821
- How much?
- 1,200.

08:42.823 --> 08:44.923
Oh, boy.Wow.
That's gonna--

08:44.925 --> 08:47.158
Bingo, wow.
Goodness gracious
with this guy.

08:47.160 --> 08:49.194
If it's not one thing,
it's another thing.
Oh, okay.

08:49.196 --> 08:52.931
But think about it this way.
If we split it, it's only
a few hundred dollars each.

08:52.933 --> 08:55.634
Great, yeah.
Let me just go grab my cash
from my money tree...

08:55.636 --> 08:58.570
that I have planted.
I know a leprechaun
who has a pot of gold.

08:58.572 --> 08:59.905
He lives at
the end of my street.

08:59.907 --> 09:01.373
Maybe I'll go to a bank
and say, "Hello.

09:01.375 --> 09:03.074
Do I have
an account here?"
Call Donald Trump!

09:03.076 --> 09:09.180
How do three men
in their 30s not have
$800 between them?

09:10.182 --> 09:12.083
They're--
The economy is in shambles.

09:12.085 --> 09:15.787
Have you taken a close look at
the marketplace right now?
The NASDAQ!

09:15.789 --> 09:16.955
Dow Jones!
It's up then down.

09:16.957 --> 09:19.925
Stop talking, goddamn it!
Fine, I'll do it!

09:19.927 --> 09:22.093
I'm not getting
my money back, am I?

09:22.095 --> 09:24.162
Give us money.

09:24.164 --> 09:25.964
Boom.

09:25.966 --> 09:26.998
What am I supposed
to do with that?

09:27.000 --> 09:29.668
You tell us.
Yeah, Bingo said you knew
how to sell those drugs.

09:29.670 --> 09:32.637
I told you not to
involve me in that!
Did you mention my name?

09:32.639 --> 09:35.307
First thing we did.
First thing we did.
You gonna harp on it all day?

09:35.309 --> 09:37.375
Goddamn it!
The guy's gonna skin me alive.

09:37.377 --> 09:39.377
- He is gonna skin you alive.
- He mentioned
something about it.

09:39.379 --> 09:42.614
Will you just pay the mob off
so we don't have to
sell these pills?

09:42.616 --> 09:44.716
Dennis, I am not using
any more of my money!

09:44.718 --> 09:47.719
- The mob is gonna kill us, man!
- Look, if I cave on this,

09:47.721 --> 09:50.255
I'm gonna be bailing
you guys out for the rest
of my life.

09:50.257 --> 09:52.190
So--
<i>I'm putting my foot down</i>
<i>on this one.</i>

09:52.192 --> 09:54.225
You bitches gotta earn
your own money!

09:54.227 --> 09:55.994
Fine, whatever!
It doesn't matter.

09:55.996 --> 09:59.230
Because-- seeing as
how I'm the boss--
You're not the boss.

09:59.232 --> 10:01.099
Oh, yes, I am.
I've come up with
an excellent idea.

10:01.101 --> 10:04.869
Frank, you are gonna get us
into that country club
that you used to belong to.

10:04.871 --> 10:06.071
And we're gonna
sell the pills there.

10:06.073 --> 10:08.840
That'd be a good place
to sell those pills.
Yes, thank you very much.

10:08.842 --> 10:12.143
You can't make no $25,000
from that amount of pills.

10:12.145 --> 10:13.979
- How long you got?
- Till Friday.

10:13.981 --> 10:17.716
Mm-mmm, you're gonna have to
turn a trick or two.
Go into prostitution.

10:17.718 --> 10:20.051
You are disgusting!
How could you suggest--

10:20.053 --> 10:23.722
I am absolutely
not doing that!
<i>I wasn't talking about you.</i>

10:23.724 --> 10:26.691
